{"symbol":"Adjunction.leftAdjointCompIso","info":"CategoryTheory.Adjunction.leftAdjointCompIso.{v_1, u_1, v_2, u_2, v_3, u_3} {C₀ : Type u_1} {C₁ : Type u_2}
  {C₂ : Type u_3} [Category.{v_1, u_1} C₀] [Category.{v_2, u_2} C₁] [Category.{v_3, u_3} C₂] {F₀₁ : C₀ ⥤ C₁}
  {F₁₂ : C₁ ⥤ C₂} {F₀₂ : C₀ ⥤ C₂} {G₁₀ : C₁ ⥤ C₀} {G₂₁ : C₂ ⥤ C₁} {G₂₀ : C₂ ⥤ C₀} (adj₀₁ : F₀₁ ⊣ G₁₀)
  (adj₁₂ : F₁₂ ⊣ G₂₁) (adj₀₂ : F₀₂ ⊣ G₂₀) (e₀₁₂ : G₂₁ ⋙ G₁₀ ≅ G₂₀) : F₀₁ ⋙ F₁₂ ≅ F₀₂
***
A natural isomorphism `G₂₁ ⋙ G₁₀ ≅ G₂₀` involving right adjoint functors
induces a natural isomorphism `F₀₁ ⋙ F₁₂ ≅ F₀₂` between the corresponding
left adjoint functors. 
***
